The paper deals with generating 3D indoor scenes using a neural network, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The use of a recursive neural network (RvNN) and variational autoencoder (VAE) involves machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) concepts. The paper also mentions semantic scene segmentation, which falls under natural language processing (CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.GR, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CL.
